Any way to automate checking of harmony rules?
I'm working through the book Harmony and Voice Leading by Schachter and Aldwell.  The book is great, especially as it has several exercises after each chapter which really help to ensure that you have learned the material.
My issue is though, that I have no quick way of checking my answers, e.g., where I have harmonized a melody.  I'm looking out for specific errors that the authors call out (e.g., chord construction errors like missing 3rds or voice leading errors like the 7th in V7 not resolving down by step).  I can if course check over my own work for these types of errors but this is time-consuming, and I also always have a nagging doubt that I may be missing something.  Is anyone aware of any tools or software which allow this type of harmony checking to be automated?  My own searches haven't turned anything up, but I find it hard to believe that such a tool doesn't exist.  I could write such a program myself, but of course don't want to spend the time if there is something freely available already.


